race.description: Bullseye Birdies Cup Day After Party Hcp (C2)
race.comment: BATTLE ON BATTLER (1) just missed two back before bumping into a progressive type here last start, beaten 3.9L that form may have been franked earlier today already. Drawn ideally for Webster with the 3kg claim coming in handy. Can go one better this time around. HILLSIDE MONARCH (7) was far too good as an odds-on favourite here last start, sitting close to the speed and running away to win impressively. Tougher here but she's open to plenty of improvement. Draws nicely and will be hard to hold out. STRYKER'S GAL (4) fitter for the first up run over 1103m at this track, finishing 4 lengths from the winner. Has a solid second up record and open to sharp improvement. TRULY GALLANT (5) won on debut last time out a week-and-a-half ago over 1210m at this track, getting home by 1.75 lengths. Solid top-three hope. SNIPPETY LEGEND (3) can feature first-up for the new stable having made the move from Victoria.
